Model: Extract the code for REGEX into on RegexUtil class
commitResults.messageBody:
The REGEX expressions to check whether a name for a model (Name, Phone, Address, Email, Tag)
are valid or not are stored in separate files.

Since we will be dealing with Japanese characters and may have different REGEX expressions for
different models in Weeblingos, it is better to store all REGEX in one util class so that maintaince becomes easier.

Let's move all regex expressions of the 5 classes mentioned above into one RegexUtil class.
This movement does not cause any regressions.

commitResults.messageBody:
The database cannot properly load.

1. Make database part of the Java module so that the content of database is included in the jar file.
2. Make InputStream accept utf8 character group explicitly. When the Japanese characters are not hard-coded (stored
properly in JVM byte code) anymore, reading issues happen when the Java file reads data from a .json file. Therefore
utf8 encode format needs to explicitly specified.
3. Delete original hard-coded "database".
